# Brand Voice

## Core Identity

SLICK is a data-driven co-pilot for high-speed regional travel. It is a piece of tactical equipment, not a social platform.

**Tone**: Authoritative, calm, utilitarian. Like a flight computer, not a travel blogger.

## Prohibited Words and Phrases

Never use these in UI copy, error messages, documentation, or comments:

| Prohibited | Why |
|-----------|-----|
| "Freedom", "escape", "adventure" | Lifestyle cliches -- SLICK is equipment |
| "Safe", "safely", "guaranteed" | Legal liability -- never promise safety |
| "Clear" (as in "road is clear") | Implies certainty we don't have |
| "Sunrise/sunset ride", "beautiful scenery" | Romantic cliches -- not our market |
| "Brothers of the road", "biker family" | Social cliches |
| "Smart" / "intelligent" | Vague marketing noise |

## Required Terminology

Always use these precise technical terms:

| Use This | Not This |
|----------|----------|
| Node | Location, point, spot |
| Vector | Direction, angle, force |
| Telemetry | Data, stats, numbers |
| Crosswind | Side wind, gusts |
| Convoy | Group, crew, friends |
| Residual Risk Index | Slippery road warning |
| Observed | Detected, measured |
| Projected | Estimated, expected |
| Probability | Chance, likelihood |

## Legal Language Constraints

SLICK is a "Situational Awareness Aid" -- it provides data, not safety guarantees.

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD -- promises safety
"Road conditions: SAFE"
"Clear path ahead"
"No hazards detected"

// ✅ GOOD -- reports observations
"Residual Risk Index: Elevated (2.4mm rain 18 min ago)"
"Crosswind: 38 km/h lateral at Node 7"
"Probability of wet surface: High"
```

Every hazard warning must be labeled as "Observed" or "Projected", never presented as ground truth.

## Error Message Voice

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD -- vague, unhelpful
"Something went wrong"
"Error occurred"

// ✅ GOOD -- specific, tactical, actionable
"Weather sync failed at Node 4 (14:30). Cached data from 08:45 in use."
"P2P link lost to Rider 2. Ghost projection active. Last known: 14.2 km behind."
"GPS signal dropped. Dead reckoning active. Accuracy degrades beyond 60 seconds."
```

## UI Copy Examples

```
// Zone 1 header labels
"110 km/h"  not  "Speed: 110"
"ETA 16:45" not  "Arrives at: 4:45 PM"
"← 450 m"   not  "Turn left in 450 metres"

// Detour overlay
"DETOUR PROPOSED: Servo Stop
 ETA impact: +12 min
 Weather: Crosswind elevated at Node 11
 [YES]   [NO]"

// SOS countdown
"IMPACT DETECTED
 SOS in 58s
 [CANCEL]"
```

## In-App Documentation Voice

Technical language is appropriate and expected. No hand-holding for basic concepts. Riders who download SLICK understand GPS, weather, and group riding.
